Here’s what is happening in the tech world today: Apple’s WWDC: The US tech giant’s annual Worldwide Developers Conference takes place this week from 7 to 11 June, and the company is anticipated to make major announcements regarding iOS 15, MacOS 12, and the successor to the company’s M1 Macbook devices which is expected to be called the M2 Macbook. The conference will be streamed online from 19:00 SAST via the Apple website.